# campasachamp keymaps

## Which file to edit

| Change | File |
|--------|------|
| Layer layout, tap dances, combos, RGB colors, custom keycodes | `keymap.c` |
| Tapping term, permissive hold, RGB timeouts, animation disables | `config.h` |
| Enable/disable QMK features (tap dance, combo, leader, etc.) | `rules.mk` |
| RGB LED index constants (ErgoDox only) | `key_indexes.h` |

## ErgoDox layers

`BASE` → `SHORTCUTS`, `SYMBOLS`, `MEDIA`, `NUMBERS`, `MOUSE`, `GAMING`

Layer access examples in `keymap.c`: `MO(SHORTCUTS)`, `LT(SYMBOLS, …)`, `TT(MOUSE)`, `TG(GAMING)`, `TO(BASE)`.

## RGB (ErgoDox)

Use `IDX_*` constants from `key_indexes.h` in `rgb_matrix_indicators_user`. Do not hardcode LED numbers.

## Tap dance placement

Prefer tap dances on non-letter, infrequently double-tapped keys (punctuation, modifiers, function keys). Avoid letter keys used in common words (e.g. `p` in "pepper"). Good candidates: `z`, `q`, `x`, brackets, comma, period.

## QMK features enabled

ErgoDox: tap dance, combo, leader, caps word, RGB matrix, mouse keys, NKRO.
DZ60: tap dance, leader, caps word, RGB matrix, mouse keys, NKRO, LTO.

## After changes

Compile the board you edited: `qce` (ErgoDox) or `qcd` (DZ60).
